<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,751,956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
C entirely coalescent with Sc; hypocostal lamina narrow, inner margin almost straight occupying 
<number box="[1259,1269,751,775]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1279,1295,751,775]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="4.0">4</number>
of length of C+ Sc; distal part of exocorium rounded, slightly narrowed apically; R parallel to C+ Sc, distinctly elevated medially and apically; M coalescent with Cu in basal part; common basal stem of M+Cu as long as half of length of mesocorium: apices of M and Cu moderately distant, slightly diverging; axial cell broadened in medial part, narrowed apically; cross-vein M-Cu faint; anal veins present; distal part of mesocorium with coriaceus area well developed; corium occupying 
<number box="[491,505,932,956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[514,526,932,956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="3.0">3</number>
of entire length of hemelytron.
</paragraph>
